description: This table contains a history of sig-related data for prescriptions, both what the provider initially prescribed and what the patient later reported taking. Most commonly, the first row for any prescription represents the sig as the prescription was written, and subsequent rows will represent changes in what the patient reports taking.

columns.name: ORDER_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier for the order record.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number for the information associated with this record. Multiple pieces of information can be associated with this record.

columns.name: PAT_ENC_CSN_ID
columns.description: The unique contact serial number for this contact. This number is unique across all patient encounters in your system. If you use IntraConnect, this is the Unique Contact Identifier (UCI).

columns.name: ENTRY_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique identifier of the user who entered the medication instructions.

columns.name: ENTRY_DTTM
columns.description: The date and time when these medication instructions were entered.

columns.name: ACTION_C_NAME
columns.description:
The action represented by this sig - e.g. the initial prescription; the pharmacist has edited the sig; or the patient reports taking this medication differently from how it was prescribed.


May contain organization-specific values: No


 Category Entries:

columns.name: SOURCE_C_NAME
columns.description:
The location from which this sig was entered.

columns.name: INFORMANT_C_NAME
columns.description:
The relationship to patient category ID for the person (as related to the patient) who reported the medication instructions for this medication.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes

columns.name: REASON_C_NAME
columns.description:
The reason given for why the patient is not taking the medication as prescribed.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes

columns.name: REASON_COMMENT
columns.description: Additional comments on the reason why the patient is not taking the medication as prescribed.

columns.name: DOSE_MIN
columns.description: The lower bound of the ranged dose for this medication's instructions.

columns.name: DOSE_UNIT_C_NAME
columns.description:
The med & dose unit category ID for the dose of this medication's instructions.


May contain organization-specific values: Yes
